{
  "id": "019d05c9-bfd2-7e20-9b4f-839cc8aef55f",
  "content": "# Graph Expansion A/B Test Results — 2026-03-19\n\nFirst quantitative comparison of vector-only vs graph-expanded retrieval on corvia's own knowledge base (8,769 entries, 11,756 edges).\n\n## Results (15 queries)\n| Metric | Graph Expand | Vector Only | Winner |\n|--------|-------------|-------------|--------|\n| Recall@5 | 76.7% | 75.6% | Graph (+1.1%) |\n| Recall@10 | 80.0% | 82.2% | Vector (+2.2%) |\n| MRR | 0.769 | 0.878 | Vector (+10.9%) |\n| Relevance | 0.734 | 0.773 | Vector (+3.9%) |\n| Latency | 1958ms | 57ms | Vector (34x faster) |\n\nPer-query: Graph wins 5, Vector wins 4, Ties 6.\n\n## Analysis\n- Graph excels at multi-hop/relationship queries (architecture, temporal, dashboard)\n- Vector excels at direct concept lookup (crash-recovery, staging, two-tier)\n- Graph adds significant latency (1.9s) for marginal quality improvement\n- Both beat the previous eval baseline significantly (was 37.5% Recall@5)\n\n## Recommendation\nConsider adaptive retrieval: detect query type and route to optimal retriever. Or default to vector with graph as an opt-in enhancement for relationship queries.",
